amilies, co-workers, friends, and neighbors, Laney's book demonstrates how the histories of German Nazism and Jim Crow in the American South intertwine in narratives about the past. This is a critical reassessment of a singular time that links the Cold War, the Space Race, and the Civil Rights era while addressing important issues of transnational science and technology, and asking Americans to consider their country's own history of racism when reflecting on the Nazi past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Apr 2020) 0aAerospace engineerszAlabamazHuntsvillexHistoryy20th century. 0aEx-NaziszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aGerman AmericanszAlabamazHuntsvillexHistoryy20th century. 0aRocketryzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213454423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300213454.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO